comment:
Public library is one shift and has very limited hours. (As of 2/23/17 check lcplin.org for updated info)
Monday: 12:30PM - 8:30PM
Tuesday: 10AM - 6PM
Wednesday: 12:30PM - 8:30PM
Thursday: 10AM - 6PM
Friday: 10AM - 6PM
Saturday: 9AM - 5PM

name: Cold Stone Creamery
comment: Employees can't really see which bathroom you use and they don't care anyway. Open minded staff. If you don't plan on buying anything you can tell the staff you just need to use the bathroom. Unless the manager is working, and older Filipino lady, then just tell her you're just looking at cakes or something.

name: Apple Store
directions: Through the door on the left side of the store and then to the right, you can ask any staff and they will point you in the right direction.

name: Park Church Co-op
directions: Down the stairs and to the left after entering through the front entrance
comment: This restroom is in the basement of a progressive and community-oriented Lutheran church. The church hosts concerts on some nights, which is the only time I have been there, but I think the restroom is available and truly gender-neutral any time the church is open.

name: Bullfrog Bagels
directions: Straight through, past the cashier.

name: Clinical & Support Options
directions: There all all gender bathrooms in the building lobby across from the elevators on the first floor and off the waiting room for the clinic on the 2nd floor.

name: Morningside Heights Branch, New York Public Library
directions: There are two gender neutral single stalls on the second floor, along the wall opposite Broadway. There is another gender neutral single stall reserved only for children and their caregivers in the children's area.
comment: You can ask at the second floor info desk if you need direction, but no key is needed. (If it is locked, someone is in it.)

name: Columbia College Plymouth Dorm
directions: the building is opened with an ID card but you can ask a student to let you in so you can use the bathroom, and then once inside the lobby you head downstairs, following the directions for the laundry room. 2 single bathrooms that are accessible and labeled "all gender"
comment: 2 single bathrooms that are accessible and labeled "all gender"! go Columbia!

name: Clinical & Support Options, Inc.
directions: 1st floor and 2nd floor are all gender.
comment: The mental health clinic is in the 2nd floor and has bathrooms available but there are also more publicly accessible bathrooms in the buildings first floor lobby.

name: Mishap Games
directions: There are two bathrooms; To get to the first one, enter the store and go straight to the back of the store; the bathroom door is to the left of the rear/emergency exit. To get to the other one, enter the store and go straight back until you find an open part in the left wall, go through there to enter the part of the store containing gaming tables, then turn and walk towards the front of that part of the store; you will find the bathroom door in the middle of the gaming table area on your left side.
comment: Unfortunately, neither bathroom is particularly accessible; the second one is a bit larger though.

name: Copytalk Business Services
directions: Enter the main plaza and follow the road around to the right until you see a wrapped balcony area.  Enter any set of the three glass doors and follow the corridor down.  You'll see a short hallway that leads to elevators and another short hallway that dead-ends.  Follow the path to the elevators to get to the Men's room (closed stall and one standing stall) or go down the dead-end hallway to reach the ladies (single seater, door has a lock).
comment: The bathrooms are shared with the upper floor businesses, but Copytalk has an unrestricted, respectful hire policy for transgender employees, so it's a much safer location.  Opens at 7am.  Likely to be most accessible before the bulk of Copytalk employees arrive after 1:00pm.

name: Eagle Creek Park Earth Discovery Center
directions: "family restroom" single stall unisex restroom located just to the left of the front reception desk (more gendered restroom facilities located in back hallway and downstairs).
comment: $5 or $6 per vehicle gate entry fee for Eagle Creek Park, no extra fee to enter Earth Discovery Center (nature/education center).  Park is open dawn-dusk, Earth Discovery Center is open 9-5 Mon-Sat, 1-5 Sun, year round, closed for most federal holidays.  Unisex Port-O-Lets also available at various locations in park during summer.

name: Marcs Southland
directions: There are two gendered single stall bathrooms next to the pharmacy, in the hallway immediately to the right of the drop off window.  No key is needed, but seemingly appears that way because the door knob doesn't turn; however, you just push the door to open.
comment: Officially for customers; if you aren't there to shop, browse closeouts for a few minutes before you go or something.
